Sri Jaya Mrutyujnaja Swami of Koodalasangama Peeth, who is leading the farmersâ€™ agitation, has said that a meet on Kalasa Banduri Nala issue would be held at Kanakanaholi village near Sindhdurg in Maharashtra on Tuesday.The seer has said that elected representatives of all the three riparian States, environmentalists, farmers and other stakeholders would be taking part in the meeting, which would be held in the presence of renowned water conservationist Rajendra Singh. Water Resources Minister M.B. Patil and Minister for Mines and Geology Vinay Kulkarni would be representing Karnataka in the meeting, the seer has said.